We recommended that Management: 

Direct the Municipal Treasurer/Property Officer to take appropriate action in maintaining Property Cards for all the PPEs of the LGU;

Direct the Municipal Accountant to maintain  Property Ledger Cards and reconcile them accordingly with the Property Cards maintained by the designated Property Officer;

Require the Municipal Accountant to prepare an itemized schedule for each PPE account to determine the composition of each PPE indicating the description, cost, and date acquired; and

Begin the process of complying with the One-Time Cleansing of PPE account balances to ensure the accuracy and reliability of the assertions regarding the existence, condition, and valuation of the PPE accounts.

Record inventory using the prescribed perpetual method of accounting on all purchased supplies and materials and use inventory tags or stock cards for monitoring;

Require the Inventory Committee and the Office of the Municipal Accountant to prepare and maintain complete SCs and SLCs, respectively, and reconcile their records regularly to ensure that all purchases and issuances are properly accounted for;

Require the Inventory Committee to conduct a comprehensive physical count of all types of inventory items semestrally prepare the RPCI and submit the same to the Auditor concerned not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively. Also, invite representative from the COA to act as a witness in the physical count; and

Submit on a quarterly basis Report on Supplies and Materials Issued to the Audit Team

